            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527231",
        "quote": "Outsiders tend to be the first to recognize the inadequacies of our social institutions. But, precisely because they are outsiders, they are usually in a poor position to fix them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527231"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Social Institutions",
                "url": "/topics/social_institutions"
            },
            {
                "name": "Them",
                "url": "/topics/them"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527232",
        "quote": "Cost is the spectre haunting health reform. For many decades, the great flaw in the American health-care system was its unconscionable gaps in coverage.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527232"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Cost",
                "url": "/topics/cost"
            },
            {
                "name": "Coverage",
                "url": "/topics/coverage"
            },
            {
                "name": "Haunting",
                "url": "/topics/haunting"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527233",
        "quote": "The health-care sector certainly employs more people and more machines than it did. But there have been no great strides in service. In Western Europe, most primary-care practices now use electronic health records and offer after-hours care; in the United States, most don't.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527233"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "United",
                "url": "/topics/united"
            },
            {
                "name": "Records",
                "url": "/topics/records"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527234",
        "quote": "There are, in human affairs, two kinds of problems: those which are amenable to a technical solution and those which are not. Universal health-care coverage belongs to the first category: you can pick one of several possible solutions, pass a bill, and (allowing for some tinkering around the edges) it will happen.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527234"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Amenable",
                "url": "/topics/amenable"
            },
            {
                "name": "Technical",
                "url": "/topics/technical"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527235",
        "quote": "The history of American agriculture suggests that you can have transformation without a master plan, without knowing all the answers up front.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527235"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Answers",
                "url": "/topics/answers"
            },
            {
                "name": "Master Plan",
                "url": "/topics/master_plan"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527237",
        "quote": "As economists have often pointed out, we pay doctors for quantity, not quality. As they point out less often, we also pay them as individuals, rather than as members of a team working together for their patients. Both practices have made for serious problems.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527237"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Point",
                "url": "/topics/point"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rather",
                "url": "/topics/rather"
            },
            {
                "name": "Individuals",
                "url": "/topics/individuals"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527240",
        "quote": "In every industrialized nation, the movement to reform health care has begun with stories about cruelty.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527240"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Cruelty",
                "url": "/topics/cruelty"
            },
            {
                "name": "Reform",
                "url": "/topics/reform"
            },
            {
                "name": "Stories",
                "url": "/topics/stories"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527241",
        "quote": "The damage that the human body can survive these days is as awesome as it is horrible: crushing, burning, bombing, a burst blood vessel in the brain, a ruptured colon, a massive heart attack, rampaging infection. These conditions had once been uniformly fatal.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527241"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Infection",
                "url": "/topics/infection"
            },
            {
                "name": "Damage",
                "url": "/topics/damage"
            },
            {
                "name": "Crushing",
                "url": "/topics/crushing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527244",
        "quote": "We now live in the era of the super-specialist - of clinicians who have taken the time to practice at one narrow thing until they can do it better than anyone who hasn't.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527244"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Practice",
                "url": "/topics/practice"
            },
            {
                "name": "Better",
                "url": "/topics/better"
            },
            {
                "name": "Era",
                "url": "/topics/era"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527245",
        "quote": "Health care confronts us with a difficult test. We have never corrected failure in something so deeply embedded in people's lives and in the economy without the pressure of an outright crisis.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527245"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Test",
                "url": "/topics/test"
            },
            {
                "name": "Crisis",
                "url": "/topics/crisis"
            },
            {
                "name": "Lives",
                "url": "/topics/lives"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527247",
        "quote": "To become a doctor, you spend so much time in the tunnels of preparation - head down, trying not to screw up, trying to make it from one day to the next - that it is a shock to find yourself at the other end, with someone shaking your hand and asking how much money you want to make.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Atul Gawande",
            "url": "/quotes/atul_gawande_527247"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Next",
